+\subsubsection{LLM-Based Literary Polish}
+Large instruction-tuned language models have been applied as a post-processing
+polish pass after NMT output, correcting stilted phrasing and improving literary
+register without retraining the backbone translation model.
+The \textit{bn-en-translate} pipeline supports an optional Ollama-based polish
+pass after the primary translation stage, with VRAM-aware sequential unloading.
+
+\textbf{Gemma~3}~\cite{gemma2025} from Google DeepMind (March 2025) provides
+strong multilingual literary quality in its 12B instruction-tuned configuration.
+In the \textit{bn-en-translate} pipeline, \texttt{gemma3:12b} replaces
+\texttt{qwen2.5:7b-instruct} as the default Ollama polish model.
+Gemma~3's 140-language training set includes Bengali, and informal evaluations
+show improved preservation of literary register and cultural references
+compared to prior defaults.
+
